{"id": "1497871305087910008", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 0, "author_id": "105316637493706752", "author_name": "tharob", "author_bot": false, "content": "Any tips on how to play it?", "timestamp": "2026-04-26T08:05:48.236000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1497871486537564220", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 0, "author_id": "191966381640646656", "author_name": "krausser", "author_bot": false, "content": "you do want a life drain on one of the units for keyflare gen, not using Kath's posse/getting a fast rouse can hurt you a bit", "timestamp": "2026-04-26T08:06:31.497000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "🙏", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1497872173644386324", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 19, "author_id": "191966381640646656", "author_name": "krausser", "author_bot": false, "content": "pretty much just sweep through your deck with Kath, use Horla's stances and vuln/weak as necessary, Loom with Arachne to gather stacks and save exalts of Tinct/Horla for a bursts(make sure to check Kath to make sure you're not overcapping on crit with the exalts, can happen sometimes depending on the relics)", "timestamp": "2026-04-26T08:09:15.316000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["105316637493706752"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1497871305087910008", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1497872331958386801", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 0, "author_id": "191966381640646656", "author_name": "krausser", "author_bot": false, "content": "you want to cycle as many hyperflares as possible, so that posse every turn and Kath exalt as often as possible to get her cards in hand helps a lot", "timestamp": "2026-04-26T08:09:53.061000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
